mediaNotes: Calls from a group of fifty or so birds mobbing me as I stood in the large, grassy marsh where they were nesting.  Typically a few of the birds would be the most vocal, while many of the others would fly around me silently.
Calling while fishing. Elevation: 2 m. Date added to IBC: June 22, 2016.
Calls from a pair of birds flying in circles over my head, as I stood at the edge of an extensive grassy marsh with a large colony of terns and gulls.
Calls from a pair of birds flying in circles over my head as I stood at the edge of the large grassy marsh that held their colony.
A group of birds calling on a colony. Monotypic.

Calls from a group of 50 or so birds near their nesting colony in a large, grassy marsh.  In this recording I took the microphone out of the parabola so that no one bird would be overly emphasized over the flock.
Calls from a half-dozen or so birds mobbing a Black Kite that was flying over their colony.  Note the different quality of the calls compared to those given when they would mob a human.
Calls from a pair of birds flying in circles over my head as I stood at the edge of the large grassy marsh that held their colony.
Calls by several birds, in a breeding colony. Monotypic. Elevation: 101 m. Date added to IBC: August 24, 2019.

Calls from a group of twenty or so birds mobbing me as I stood in the large, grassy marsh where they were nesting.  Typically one or two of the birds would be the most vocal, while many of the others would fly around me silently.
calls from flock feeding in sewage treatment pond
Two birds calling in flight. Elevation: 117 m. Date added to IBC: June 22, 2016.
